    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="420"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 P.W./8–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-11">August 11,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received August 11—11:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2264. White House Nbr 325 from the Secretary of State requesting delivery of a
                    message from the President to the Prime Minister<note n="62" xml:id="d420fn1"
                        >See first paragraph of Extract of Minutes, <ref target="#pg_634">p.
                            634</ref>.</note> was telephoned to the Prime Minister, who is at
                    Chequers, within five minutes of its receipt at the Embassy.</p>
                <p>The Prime Minister asked me to forward the following message to the President:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In reply to your message in regard to your proposals for the acceptance
                            of the Japanese surrender I am in accord with the general <pb
                                facs="0652" n="640" xml:id="pg_640"/> procedure you propose and I
                            designate Admiral Sir Bruce Austin Fraser<note n="62a" xml:id="d420fn2"
                                >Commander in Chief of the British Pacific Fleet.</note> our
                            representative.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
